children.subject: I think you'll be able to handle it. I took 61B, 61C, and 100 in a semester previously, which should be comparable.

61C is a LOT of work. And by a lot I actually mean a lot, when I took it it was ~4 hours a day on it (hw, lab, project, etc). 70 is conceptually hard and pset lengths vary dependent on professor. If you have really good intuition on those topics, it is fine but otherwise I'd say do not stack other stuff on top. Data 100 was okay for me, a manageable workload and pretty well-organized. I'd say workload-wise it should be manageable (but expect it to be as heavy if not heavier than this sem), but your brain will be tired.

history.content:
For reference, I took 61A, 16A, Math 53, and a breadth in Fa20, and I'm currently taking 61B, 16B, and 2 breadths this semester. Both schedules have been pretty manageable for me, but this semester has been a bit on the busy side.


Also, I'm not planning on taking any other classes besides 61C, 70, and Data 100 for Fa21.


Thanks in advance!
history.subject: Is 61C + 70 + Data 100 a reasonable schedule?
